sql:
SELECT users.user_name
FROM users
WHERE users.user_id IN (
  SELECT trial_access.user_id
  FROM trial_access
)
AND users.user_id NOT IN (
  SELECT condition_access.user_id
  FROM condition_access
);

external_knowledge:
- "places" refers to the institutions where experiments are conducted;
- "researchers" refers to the users who are involved in the experiments;
- "accessed the system" refers to both condition and response access events.
